code:

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['diff'] = data['u'] - data['v']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.hist(data['diff'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'mean={data["diff"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['diff'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'median={data["diff"].median():.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Difference between u and v')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of the difference between u and v?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
